<p><b>I registered for a Multiverse user account, but I haven't received 
the confirmation email!</b></p>

<p>
The confirmation email was probably stopped by a spam filter.
Please check your spam folders or try adding Multiverse to your whitelist
and re-register.  
If all else fails, email <script>mailLink("info")</script><noscript>[<i>Please enable JavaScript to view email address</i>]</noscript>.
</p>

<p><b>SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS</b></p>

<p>
<b>Q: What are the minimum system requirements?</b>
<br><b>A</b>: The Multiverse World Browser requires:
<ul class="text"><li> Operating System: Windows XP or Vista
</li><li> Processor: Pentium 4 with 1GHz or greater (2GHz+ recommended)
</li><li> RAM: 512 MB (1 GB+ recommended)
</li><li> Video Card: DirectX 9 compatible. Pixel shader and vertex shader 
compatible hardware with 128MB of texture memory (256MB recommended).
</li><li> Sound Card: DirectSound compatible audio hardware</li></ul>
</p>
<p>
<b>Important</b>: The most common problem with running the Multiverse World Browser is 
not having the proper graphics card.  
See <a href="http://update.multiverse.net/wiki/index.php/Supported_Graphics_Cards">Supported Graphics Cards</a> 
for a list of supported graphics cards.
</p>
<p>
<b>Q: Does Multiverse support 64-bit Windows?</b>
<br><b>A</b>: Yes, the Multiverse World Browser supports 64-bit Windows.
</p>

<p>
<b>Q: Does Multiverse support localized (non-English) versions of Windows?</b>
<br><b>A</b>: Yes, the Multiverse World Browser and tools support localized 
installations of Windows.
</p>

<p>
<b>Q: What about other platforms, like Macintosh and Linux?</b>
<br><b>A</b>: Support for other platforms is on the roadmap.
</p>

<p>
<b>Q: What type of Internet connection will I need?</b>
<br><b>A</b>: You should have a broadband connection, such as DSL, Cable, or better.
</p>

<p><b>USING The MULTIVERSE WORLD BROWSER (CLIENT)</b></p>
<p>
See <a href="http://www.multiverse.net/doc/client/demoworld.html">Using the Multiverse Client in Demo World</a> for complete information.
</p>

<p>
<b>Q: How do I control the camera?</b>
<ul class="text"><li> Right-click and drag to look around and change the direction
your character is facing. 
</li><li> Left-click and drag to look around without changing the direction your
character is facing. 
</li><li>Use the mouse wheel to zoom in and out.</li></ul>
</p>
<p>
